description.2: As the truth is revealed about Onslaught, Alistaire Stuart and Rory Campbell join the ranks of Black Air.
description.3: The Incredible Hulk is no more! Is it really possible that the Hulk has finally been destroyed once and for all? And how do the ones closest to Bruce Banner cope with the news? A special issue starring Betty Ross and Jen Walters, the She-Hulk!
description.4: Young Tony Stark battles the foe called Frostbite!
description.5: Ben's life is a whirlwind of turmoil from the plot against him and Peter, and it gets even worse when the Hobgoblin strikes!
description.6: Miguel has to deal with an undersea threat from New Atlantis both as the CEO of Alchemax and as Spider-Man!
description.7: Thor, Victor, and the rest of the Prazniki family are sucked into another one of Loki's traps! A bright flash transports them all far away!
description.9: Reed Richards and Namor duke it out for the love of the Invisible Woman! It's a medieval duel with super powers! Nuff' said!
description.10: Wolverine continues to regress into an animal at the hands of Genesis. Professor Xavier uses his abilities in an ethically-unsound manner. Plus, the first appearance of Ozymandias, immortal servant to Apocalypse!
description.19: The Leader sets his stakes on capturing the Hulk. X-Factor joins the X-Men to free the Jade Giant...before the Hulk turns his rampage on his rescuers!
description.21: Peter Parker de-powered and brutally attacked! Ben Reilly's life sabotaged! And just when he thinks it couldn't get any worse - someone knows Spider-Man's secret!
description.22: Hercules and Deathcry decide to take some personal time...on Earth's moon! But will their trip go off without a hitch? Back at the mansion, Black Widow confronts Masque when she suspects the Avenger has ulterior motives. Plus, a dangerous intruder at Avengers Mansion!
description.27: Luke Skywalker'has been bereft of'the Force'for some time now, and has had to rely on his wits and cunning to stay out of the hands of the Imperials. Now, disguised as a'bounty hunter'with the beautiful and lethal Mara Jade'as his prisoner, he has to find'Captain'Talon Karrde, rescue'Han from the Empire's clutches, and reunite with the other architects of the Rebellion. But even if Luke and Han prevail, the Rebellion may be on the verge of destruction, unraveling itself in a bloody civil war!
description.28: Even as Darth Vader and his Imperial garrison approach Mimban from the air, Luke and Leia find that their biggest problems lie under the planet's crust. For deep in the soil lives Mimban's deadliest predator-perhaps the galaxy's deadliest predator-the gigantic, wormlike wandrella; and if the humongous wandrella can't catch them, the subterranean race of aboriginals-the Coway-just might!
description.29: A cloaking device isn't easy to come by-even a long time ago in a galaxy far, far away. But when the members of Rogue Squadron try to pick one up from the super-scientific alien inventors known as the Mrlssi, they find they've been accused of every crime from burglary to murder, and that the Empire will stop at nothing to bring them in!
description.30: Doctor Strange returns to New York to fight a mighty demon!
description.31: Wolverine, Apocalypse’s Horseman of Death? He may regain his Adamantium, but will Logan lose his mind? And what does the fruition of Genesis’ plan mean for the Dark Riders and Cyber? The return of feral Wolverine!
description.32: WEB OF CARNAGE reaches its thrilling conclusion! Spider-Carnage grows more and more vicious with each passing moment, and Ben Reilly decides that there's only one man that can help him control the raging symbiote - Cletus Kasady, the original Carnage!
description.35: THE BIRTH OF SPIDER-CARNAGE! While Cletus rots in jail, the sick symbiote is carving up The Big Apple! The only way for Spidey to stop it is to combine with it and become- the amazing Spider-Carnage! Continued in SPIDER-MAN #67!
description.36: The Hulk's arch-nemesis Leader conceives a plan that involves the destruction of world famous landmarks. But by the time the Avengers catch wind of this plot, will it be too late to stop the Leader's reign of terror?
description.39: As Douglock comes further undone, Excalibur ramps up their battle against Black Air. The London Hellfire Club delves into arcane ritual.
description.40: The Hulk is on a rampage of destruction unlike any he's ever committed before, and only the mighty Thor stands in his way!
description.41: Iron Man gets a new love interest and takes off in a new direction. Featuring the Avengers!
description.42: RUN FOR YOUR LIVES, HERE COMES SPIDER-CARNAGE! Spidey's melded with a sinister symbiote and only a hated enemy can stop him!' It's Spider-Carnage vs. Kaine— but which one's the good guy?!
description.43: Spider-Man: defender of Alchemax?! When a worker's revolt leads to terrorist raids, the wall-crawler may find himself in the ironic role as Alchemax's last hope!
description.44: Razorfist and Spiral end up being the foolish ones when they try fooling Thor into one of their crazy schemes!
description.45: Will Spidey be able to help the police capture a dangerous crime group called the Enforcers?
description.47: Black Bolt goes berserk, the Inhumans are running scared, and the Invisible Woman undergoes a major status quo change!'
description.48: Bobby Drake decides to "break the ice" with Emma Frost, by confronting her at Frost Enterprises. What words will Iceman exchange with the woman who overthrew his life? And what blows will be dealt? Plus, Beast faces catastrophe in the laboratory, while Gambit and Bishop attempt to reconcile.
description.51: The psycho symbiote is on the loose- but Cletus Kasady is still locked up in Ravencroft! What gives? This issue begins a four-part blockbuster in which Spidey risks death - and a fate worse than death - to find the answer! Continued in AMAZING SPIDER-MAN #410!
description.55: Wolverine develops a special bond with Hulk while the two berserkers are captive at the Hulkbuster base! X-Factor guest stars!
description.65: "Mos Eisley Spaceport. You'll never find a more wretched hive of scum and villainy." With those words, Obi-Wan Kenobi introduced the most famous, not to mention dangerous, drinking establishment in the history of science fiction. Now, you can get a table of your own. Belly up to the bar and let the patrons regale you with a tale of Tatooine, a story of interstellar romance, and a saga of Rebel triumph. And please be sure to check your droids and your blaster at the door.
description.66: Mara Jade'has survived for most of her life among the worst riffraff in'the galaxy. Years ago, she posed as a dancer in the decadent court of the late Jabba'the'Hutt. It was there that she first witnessed'Luke's'awesome powers of'Jedi'mind-control. Now, in the steaming jungles of'Myrkr, Luke and'Artoo'are Jade's helpless captives. Jade is determined to finish off her Jedi prisoner, once she's finished stripping him of his Jedi secrets!
description.67: If Wedge Antilles can't persuade the alien Mrlssi to sell their cloaking device to the New Republic, the result could be disaster. And that's just what Wedge expects when he discovers that the negotiating party includes Loka Hask -- the pirate chieftain who killed Wedge's parents!
description.68: This is it! Wolverine’s showdown with Genesis of the Clan Akkaba! Luckily for Logan, Cannonball’s not far behind. Will Cyber’s Adamantium restore Wolverine to his former prime?
description.70: Mordo's daughter has transferred cancer over to one of Strange's loved ones in a sick twist.
description.74: Spider-Man discovers a shocking truth in a Manhattan morgue - a skeleton wearing a Spidey costume of its own! Who was this person, and what does their identity mean for Ben Reilly's future as Spider-Man?
description.75: A team-up of cosmic proportions! Spider-Man has fallen victim to the plot of the Mad Thinker, and his mind is under the madman's control! Only one person can save him: the rider of the space ways, Silver Surfer!
description.76: This is it! After fighting Tendril to the bitter end, Peter Parker's life will be changed forever! Like it or not, one thing is certain in this issue: this is the end of Spider-Man!
description.80: THE RETURN OF KAINE continues! Kaine has eluded the Great Game for now, but the Rhino won't stop until Kaine joins up - whether he likes it or not! He'll have to team up with Spidey to get out of this one in one piece!
description.81: The Avengers take on two members of the Zodiac! Meanwhile, a teenaged Tony Stark makes a valiant attempt at creating a temporal gateway. Will all of Manhattan pay the price in Kang's master plan?
description.83: Terrorists have holed up inside the Lincoln Memorial. Their demands don't include getaways or money-they simply want Captain America. And if their demands aren't met, they'll blow themselves up, along with everyone inside the memorial!
description.91: Excalibur reluctantly battles X-Man, who believes that the team and Moira are out to get him!
description.92: The Hulk comes face to face with what may be his greatest enemy! But this showdown is unlike any he's ever faced before! For this enemy lives within his own mind - and is known only as THE MAESTRO!
description.93: Captain America, Thor, and Iron Man take on a new Zodiac. But in a world without energy, how can Stark recharge his suit?
description.94: The explosive finale to THE RETURN OF KAINE! At last, the fateful showdown you've been waiting for: Ben Reilly vs. Kaine in a fight to the finish! Is there anything left of the heroism Spidey once saw in the wayward clone?
description.95: It's been a dark time for Miguel O'Hara and the funeral for Dana is only going to make things worse. Can anyone restore Miguel's faith in himself?
description.96: Guest-starring Captain America! The Enchantress lends a hand to Thor in battle, while the Zodiac's evil machinations continue to unfold.
description.97: What happens when Electro and the 'Doctor' have Spider-Man's mind under their control? Who will save Spider-Man when he can't save himself!?
description.99: Mr. Fantastic returns to Four Freedoms Plaza, but can he squeeze back into the hearts of those he left behind? The Inhumans crash the scene with news that their leader Black Bolt, is now a deranged tyrant! What has happened to the once-peaceful king of the Inhumans? Plus, a love triangle emerges between Lyja, Johnny, and Ben!

0.text: This is it! Storm's final confrontation with Mikhail Rasputin will leave you reeling. Dark Beast makes a twisted revelation about the Age of Apocalypse.

1.text: Matt and Foggy add Lady Mastermind to their client roster!

5.text: Ben's life is a whirlwind of turmoil from the plot against him and Peter, and it gets even worse when the Hobgoblin strikes!

11.text: Can Dark Beast and Gambit stop Mister Sinister before he mind-wipes Bishop’s final memories?

13.text: Continued from last issue! X-Force is pegged for the death of the Externals. The NYPD may try to shake loose a confession, but another mutant, still roaming free, is behind this massacre!

14.text: Holocaust is after X-Man… but who sent him? Nate and Threnody continue to grow closer.

16.text: Has Synch truly turned on his classmates?!

18.text: Spidey must stop Hammerhead when he threatens the Daily Bugle!

20.text: On his way to Ebonshire, Nathan comes across a fallen pirate ship. Onboard, Nathan finds Umbridge, and tries to save her from an attack by insectoid creatures. Overwhelmed, Nathan and Umbrige are saved by Aliya, and the trio journey to Madame Sanctity. With Sanctity’s support, Nathan is invited into the Askani fold.

23.text: Nate Grey's powers are exploding out of control, and only Cable can stop him in time! But after learning Nate's dark secrets…will he even want to?

24.text: MAN WITHOUT A COUNTRY PART 2 Exiled to foreign soil by the very country he is sworn to serve, Steve Rogers must don a new costume to clear his name and save the world yet again!

25.text: Green Goblin battles Angel Face…and then must take on Salt & Pepper!

26.text: Venom tries to find a serial killer that is a predator of his symbiote suit! But he quickly becomes the hunted.

30.text: Doctor Strange returns to New York to fight a mighty demon!

31.text: Wolverine, Apocalypse’s Horseman of Death? He may regain his Adamantium, but will Logan lose his mind? And what does the fruition of Genesis’ plan mean for the Dark Riders and Cyber? The return of feral Wolverine!

32.text: WEB OF CARNAGE reaches its thrilling conclusion! Spider-Carnage grows more and more vicious with each passing moment, and Ben Reilly decides that there's only one man that can help him control the raging symbiote - Cletus Kasady, the original Carnage!

34.text: MAN WITHOUT A COUNTRY PART 1 Captain America has been branded a traitor by the U.S. Government! Where will he go and how can he clear his name?

37.text: CABLE VS. X-MAN! Plus: the stunning secret of their true connection revealed!

38.text: With a renewed sense of self and his identity crisis behind him, Daredevil begins his nightly prowls once more!

42.text: RUN FOR YOUR LIVES, HERE COMES SPIDER-CARNAGE! Spidey's melded with a sinister symbiote and only a hated enemy can stop him!' It's Spider-Carnage vs. Kaine— but which one's the good guy?!

49.text: The X-Men investigate a subway train filled with mutated humans!

51.text: The psycho symbiote is on the loose — but Cletus Kasady is still locked up in Ravencroft! What gives? This issue begins a four-part blockbuster in which Spidey risks death — and a fate worse than death — to find the answer! Continued in AMAZING SPIDER-MAN #410!

52.text: The epic conclusion to Ben Reilly's first encounter with Venom! Eddie Brock is fighting both Spider-Man and the influence of the symbiote in his own mind! Who will win, and who will survive?

53.text: This issue offers a glimpse into the fraught relationship between Ororo and Forge. What really drove a wedge between this former couple? Plus, the true terror of Gene Nation is revealed.

54.text: Spider-Man disagrees with the way the Punisher fights and tries to stop him!

55.text: Wolverine develops a special bond with Hulk while the two berserkers are captive at the Hulkbuster base! X-Factor guest stars!

56.text: FINAL ISSUE! In the aftermath of "The Crossing," Force Works attempts to rebuild, but is the damage -- to the HQ, to the team, to their lives -- too much to repair?

57.text: Liz Osborn and her lawyers go after Green Goblin with a cease-and-desist letter! Will this case make it to court?

58.text: Surprise revelations jump-start a new beginning for War Machine! Will Jim Rhodes turn his back on Earth to seek his destiny in the stars?

59.text: Caliban and Sunspot…wanted for MURDER?! Absalom and Crule blame X-Force for the death of Gideon, the External. Warpath knows the true culprit, but he’s not in any position to spill!

60.text: X-Man teams up with Cable to take on Exodus in all-out battle!

62.text: Bishop lends a hand against Emplate!

64.text: Nathan and his comrade Tetherblood wet their whistle at a “milk” bar. After getting into an argument, a New Canaanite ‘Strator confronts both men and questions their allegiance to New Canaan. Meanwhile, Stryfe and Ch'Vayre head to Egypt to disrupt the tomb of En Sabah Nur. Will Stryfe regain the powers of Apocalypse, and resurrect an Age of Destruction?

68.text: This is it! Wolverine’s showdown with Genesis of the Clan Akkaba! Luckily for Logan, Cannonball’s not far behind. Will Cyber’s Adamantium restore Wolverine to his former prime?

69.text: A Beast-centric issue! While Dark Beast extracts details from Beast’s life, Hank McCoy of the X-Men tries to find a cure for the Legacy Virus. Will Dark Beast prove to have a stronger hold over the X-Men?

70.text: Mordo's daughter has transferred cancer over to one of Strange's loved ones in a sick twist.

71.text: Shatterstar faces a cold truth when he loses a duel to Warpath. Meanwhile, the coming Onslaught is hinted at when Meltdown (formerly Boom-Boom), Domino and Siryn confront the Blob.

72.text: DELIVER HER FROM EVIL! When Threnody is threatened by the Marauders, X-Man swoops in to save the day!

75.text: A team-up of cosmic proportions! Spider-Man has fallen victim to the plot of the Mad Thinker, and his mind is under the madman's control! Only one person can save him: the rider of the space ways, Silver Surfer!

76.text: This is it! After fighting Tendril to the bitter end, Peter Parker's life will be changed forever! Like it or not, one thing is certain in this issue: this is the end of Spider-Man!

77.text: The fight between Spidey and Venom takes a harrowing turn when Anne gets caught in the crossfire! Will the life of his former love help Eddie Brock overcome the beast within?

78.text: Mikhail Rasputin – alive? Colossus' brother is revealed to be living and well. Storm seeks vengeance for his crimes against mutantkind.

82.text: Cable prepares for his inevitable showdown with the enigmatic Nate Grey! But there's only one problem -- he'll have to face him ALONE!

84.text: In the aftermath of Avengers: Timeslide, Force Works faces the fact that the team is finished. But how will they respond to the Avenger's pressures?

85.text: Green Goblin and Daredevil team up to protect his Uncle Ben from an assassination attempt!

86.text: TIMESLIDE cleaned War Machine's clock. Now, Rhodes is forced to break in a new set of armor!

87.text: Doom reflects on his dream of a Utopian world order, including a reliance on nanotechnology and the debts owed him by humankind.

88.text: Concluding the fully-painted look at the secret origin of Spider-Man! The turning point that decided Spidey's career--he has the power, but will he accept the responsibility?

89.text: The Final Fate of Phoenix! You won't want to miss this final issue!

90.text: Matt must fight his demons to find his identity and purpose!

94.text: The explosive finale to THE RETURN OF KAINE! At last, the fateful showdown you've been waiting for: Ben Reilly vs. Kaine in a fight to the finish! Is there anything left of the heroism Spidey once saw in the wayward clone?
